    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="334"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/126</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_COT1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crosby</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 16.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1"
                            >Lansing</persName>
                    </hi>: I beg leave to acknowledge receipt of memorandum of your Department dated
                    October 10<note n="1" xml:id="d334fn1">Not printed.</note> transmitting a
                    communication from Ambassador <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1"
                        >Willard</persName>, in relation to possible demands for the export of gold
                    to Spain, which demands the Ambassador <pb facs="0456" n="1210" xml:id="pg_1210"
                    /> thinks may be in the interest of certain persons who are very close to
                    Germany.</p>
                <p>In response permit me to say that since the embargo was placed on gold, no
                    shipments of gold to that country have been licensed, and all applications now
                    being received by the board for Spain are refused.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_COT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Oscar Crosby</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
